Text: Not getting your period sounds crazy right? But, when you’re on birth control, it’s normal and totally ok - especially for the really effective types like the IUD or the implant. And even if you’re on other types of birth control like the pill, patch, or ring, you can skip your period by just starting your new birth control the week of your period instead of taking the placebo pills.

Text: If you think you might be pregnant, you can take a pregnancy test to find out for sure. But you’ll need to wait at least 3 weeks after you had unprotected sex for an at-home test or urine test at a doctor’s office to give you real results.
